from test: 40 Bockris and Minevski46 showed that Cl− was incorporated into the oxide film and that the Cl− depth concentration profile changed before and after breakdown, Figure 10. Other than the difference in Cl− concentration, there does not appear to be any differences in the oxide film thickness before and after breakdown. An important conclusion from this paper is that Cl− entrainment would at best make a minor contribution to the total Cl− concentration.
from Soup: 40 Bockris and Minevski 46 showed that Cl − was incorporated into the oxide film and that the Cl − depth concentration profile changed before and after breakdown, Figure 10 . Other than the difference in Cl − concentration, there does not appear to be any differences in the oxide film thickness before and after breakdown. An important conclusion from this paper is that Cl − entrainment would at best make a minor contribution to the total Cl − concentration.
